This paper deals with the problem of subspace clustering, which is a common task in computer vision and machine learning. The paper proposes a new model that combines low rank subspace clustering with graph regularization, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision and machine learning for improving clustering results. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves optimization techniques and regularization, which are common topics in machine learning and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The paper also involves matrix decomposition and clustering, which are topics in data science, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible category. Finally, the paper involves the use of graph regularization, which is a technique commonly used in information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible category as well.
